# Jinja2 Template Conventions

## Template Map

| Template | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `index.html` | Landing page |
| `test_list.html` | Home page — list all tests |
| `test_detail.html` | Single test overview with skill cards |
| `test_section.html` | Reading Practice Mode |
| `test_mode_section.html` | Reading Test Mode |
| `listening_section.html` | Listening Practice Mode (JS state machine) |
| `listening_test_mode_section.html` | Listening Test Mode (JS state machine) |
| `answer_key.html` | Standard answer key |
| `comprehensive_answer_key.html` | Full results with statistics |
| `login.html` | OAuth login page |
| `vocabulary_notes.html` | Vocabulary notes management |
| `session_cleared.html` | Session cleared confirmation |
| `test_content_partial.html` | Reusable test content fragment |

## UI Theme

- CELPIP-style professional interface
- Reading: default theme
- Listening Practice: blue theme (`#003366`)
- Listening Test: red theme (`#c8102e`)
- Two-column layout: passage (left) + questions (right)
- Timer with visual warnings (yellow at 60s, red at critical)

## Listening Templates — State Machine

The listening templates contain significant JavaScript for the state machine:
- `steps` array passed from Python via Jinja2 (built in `prepare_test_data()`)
- States: passage playback → question display
- Parts 1-3: Split-pane with per-question audio and 30s countdown
- Parts 4-6: Full-width with inline dropdown selects
- Practice Mode: replay, skip, back/forward navigation
- Test Mode: play-once, auto-play, forward-only, no skip in audio state

## Dropdown Pattern

Reading and Listening Parts 4-6 use inline dropdowns:
- `__DROPDOWN_X__` in JSON content → replaced by `<select>` HTML in `data_loader.py`
- After selection, dropdown is replaced by a styled `<span>` showing the completed sentence
- Clicking the span re-opens the dropdown

## Vocabulary Notes Integration

All test section templates include:
- Floating `📚 Add Vocabulary Note` button (bottom-left, authenticated users only)
- Modal popup for quick note entry
- Recent notes preview (last 5 for current part)
